# Volcano

Volcano is a serverless platform for building and deploying apps and AI agents.

This plugin exposes Volcano skills through `plugins/cursor/skills`, a plugin-local git submodule pointing at `https://github.com/Kong/volcano-skills`. It does not copy or fork the skill content.

Canonical sources:

- Plugin skills submodule: `plugins/cursor/skills`
- Source repository: `https://github.com/Kong/volcano-skills`
- Default web origin: `https://volcano.dev`

## Before any Volcano work

1. Use the plugin-shipped `AGENTS.md` and `volcano-*` skills from this plugin's `skills/` directory.
2. If the `volcano` CLI is missing or stale, run `/install-volcano`. That command installs the CLI if missing or runs `volcano upgrade` if already installed. It does not download skills into `~/.volcano/skills`.
3. Prefer the `volcano` CLI for Volcano actions. Use `volcano <area> --help` and `--json` where useful.

## Safety

Follow the safety model in the plugin-shipped `AGENTS.md`. In particular, production deploys, deletions, secret/variable changes, permission/visibility changes, custom domains, and billing/account changes require explicit user confirmation.
